255
00:21:52,640 --> 00:22:16,312
Rym: Games journalists superficially kept comparing it to Overwatch, so players thought that they would be equivalent games, so I get the impression that the Overwatch-- people who were playing Overwatch or would play Overwatch, people who like a competitive first-person shooter, thought that Battleborn would be some sort of first-person or third-person competitive shooter, but when they got into it, despite what it looked like, it was a MOBA.

256
00:22:17,095 --> 00:22:23,756
Rym: Generally, the kind of person who plays a first-person shooter, competitively, is not equally enthused about a MOBA.

257
00:22:23,816 --> 00:22:29,040
Rym: Like, they target-- while there's a lot of overlap, they do target fundamentally different game experiences.

258
00:22:29,620 --> 00:22:38,080
